WEBVTT

00:09.885 --> 00:11.552
D'oh!

00:21.747 --> 00:24.189
♪<i> Gather round, me buckos</i> ♪

00:24.358 --> 00:26.416
♪<i> A story I will tell</i> ♪

00:26.518 --> 00:28.252
♪<i> Of a woman named Lily</i> ♪

00:28.353 --> 00:30.420
♪<i> Who cast quite a spell</i> ♪

00:30.522 --> 00:32.606
♪<i> It started back in Britain</i> ♪

00:32.700 --> 00:34.700
♪<i> It started in a pub...</i> ♪

00:34.893 --> 00:36.518
(overlapping shouting)

00:36.620 --> 00:39.112
-She's mine.
-It's<i> my</i> birthday.

00:39.206 --> 00:41.189
She's mine.

00:41.208 --> 00:42.766
(bagpipes honking)

00:42.826 --> 00:45.544
I can't be the cause of this.

00:45.695 --> 00:47.271
-I'm leaving.
-MAN: Your fault!

00:47.289 --> 00:49.364
-(grunts)
-(groans)

00:49.425 --> 00:52.367
♪<i> We were fighting over Lily</i>
<i> using knife, fork and club.</i> ♪

00:52.428 --> 00:55.054
That's all I got.
The rest will be spoken word.

00:55.247 --> 00:57.798
(guitar plays melody)

00:57.950 --> 00:59.224
Lily gets why we're here.

00:59.393 --> 01:01.118
Life is supposed to be fun.

01:01.220 --> 01:02.953
I loved her. We all loved her.

01:03.013 --> 01:06.231
The way gophers love
that sweet, sweet poison.

01:08.352 --> 01:11.719
Every man wanted her for
the greatest reason there is.

01:11.822 --> 01:13.847
Lily could make life fun.

01:13.908 --> 01:15.365
♪ ♪

01:17.361 --> 01:20.470
Now everyone,
hold hands with a stranger.

01:20.531 --> 01:22.155
-Oh, pleased to meet you.
-(overlapping greetings)

01:22.308 --> 01:23.916
MAN:
How delightful.

01:24.109 --> 01:25.918
♪ ♪

01:26.087 --> 01:30.005
<i> Lily! (giggling)</i>

01:31.592 --> 01:35.010
-MAN: Good one, Lily.
-(laughter, applause)

01:39.291 --> 01:41.558
(clock chiming)

01:43.604 --> 01:44.845
-(electricity crackles)
-(cheering)

01:44.939 --> 01:46.087
MAN:
Thanks, Lily!

01:46.190 --> 01:47.755
Pub's back open!

01:47.775 --> 01:50.109
But like The Beatles
and balmy weather,

01:50.302 --> 01:52.427
she was too hot
for England to handle.

01:52.488 --> 01:56.097
I find you far too alluring
for the average Englishman

01:56.117 --> 02:00.619
and banish you to Britain's
penal colony, America.

02:03.440 --> 02:05.198
<i> This is your captain speaking.</i>

02:05.292 --> 02:07.960
<i> -Will you date me?</i>
-Sorry. No.

02:08.111 --> 02:11.446
<i> Uh, okay. I'm experiencing</i>
<i> some emotional turbulence.</i>

02:11.465 --> 02:13.114
<i> My life is pathetic.</i>

02:13.175 --> 02:16.468
<i> Going back and forth,</i>
<i> back and forth.</i>

02:16.620 --> 02:19.454
<i> (crying):</i>
<i> I don't want to live anymore.</i>

02:19.515 --> 02:24.143
<i> WILLIE:</i>
<i> Even the most glamorous movie</i>
<i> stars of Hollywood bored her.</i>

02:24.294 --> 02:26.887
Oh, farewell, Leo.
You're a lovely boy,

02:26.981 --> 02:30.649
but my heart isn't some CGI bear
for you to conquer.

02:30.842 --> 02:33.301
But I've completely opened
myself up to you.

02:33.362 --> 02:35.687
I even admitted I play
the same guy in every role.

02:35.839 --> 02:37.063
Marry me!

02:37.158 --> 02:38.732
Oh, maybe I should
go back to England.

02:38.826 --> 02:40.884
No. Give this country a chance.

02:40.986 --> 02:42.552
Don't judge us by Hollywood.

02:42.654 --> 02:44.388
All right,
but I'm leaving now, dear.

02:44.406 --> 02:45.664
You'll have to content yourself

02:45.815 --> 02:47.908
with generic supermodels,
I'm afraid.

02:48.043 --> 02:50.335
Nothing ever works out for me.

02:51.529 --> 02:52.987
<i> WILLIE:</i>
<i> She needed to get away.</i>

02:53.090 --> 02:54.731
<i> Somewhere. Anywhere.</i>

02:54.791 --> 02:56.733
<i> So she threw a dart.</i>

02:56.752 --> 02:58.552
Hmm, what's next?

02:59.555 --> 03:01.638
♪ ♪

03:04.226 --> 03:06.092
<i> WILLIE:</i>
<i> So she headed to Springfield,</i>

03:06.245 --> 03:09.079
<i> little knowing that its men</i>
<i> had the lowest testosterone,</i>

03:09.097 --> 03:12.357
<i> not counting the Columbia</i>
<i> University football team.</i>

03:12.526 --> 03:16.102
<i> Lily wanted peace,</i>
<i> but the best-laid plans...</i>

03:16.197 --> 03:17.921
<i> (babbles)</i>

03:17.981 --> 03:20.106
<i> Can't understand me? Too bad.</i>

03:20.201 --> 03:22.016
<i> I'm your narrator.</i>

03:22.119 --> 03:23.851
<i> Do not tell me...</i>

03:23.954 --> 03:26.121
<i> (babbling)</i>

03:27.041 --> 03:28.598
Hmm.

03:28.659 --> 03:31.451
The only thing worse
than when you guys yap

03:31.587 --> 03:33.620
is you sitting here
all quiet and sullen.

03:33.772 --> 03:36.215
I ain't sullen, I'm lachrymose.

03:36.408 --> 03:39.551
Oh, why did I give him
that stupid word-a-day calendar?

03:39.720 --> 03:42.012
Hmm. Impulsinicity?

03:43.057 --> 03:44.448
Uh, excuse me, there, lady,

03:44.508 --> 03:46.558
but, uh, this is a man's bar.

03:46.710 --> 03:50.562
And I'd like a man's drink.
Bourbon, neat, in a dirty glass.

03:50.755 --> 03:52.231
You got it. Whoa.

03:52.424 --> 03:54.650
Just got to look up
what "neat" means.

03:55.653 --> 03:57.753
I just don't understand.

03:57.821 --> 03:59.387
Understand what?

03:59.448 --> 04:01.889
What's a pub without a song?

04:01.909 --> 04:06.820
♪<i> At the pub at the crossroads,</i>
<i> there's whiskey and beer...</i> ♪

04:06.956 --> 04:08.914
There are songs about drinking?

04:09.107 --> 04:13.585
♪<i> There's brandy, strong cognac</i>
<i> that's aging for years</i> ♪

04:13.778 --> 04:17.923
♪<i> But for killing the thirst</i>
<i> and for easing the gout</i> ♪

04:18.116 --> 04:22.243
♪<i> There's nothing at all</i>
<i> beats a pint of good stout</i> ♪

04:22.304 --> 04:25.171
♪<i> Pint of good stout.</i> ♪

04:26.124 --> 04:27.991
Oh, what's that
I hear you asking?

04:28.010 --> 04:29.584
Where are the Simpsons?

04:29.645 --> 04:32.162
Haven't you heard enough
about the bloody Simpsons

04:32.222 --> 04:34.331
to last a thousand lifetimes?

04:34.391 --> 04:36.257
Well, I guess not.

04:36.318 --> 04:40.028
So, Homer is about to receive
an unpleasant surprise.

04:40.990 --> 04:42.355
What a great day.

04:42.491 --> 04:44.858
I've never been so happy.

04:44.952 --> 04:47.619
Nothing can ruin it. Nothing.

04:47.788 --> 04:49.121
What? Where you going?

04:49.314 --> 04:50.847
On our vacation, remember?

04:50.949 --> 04:53.350
My aunt's letting us
use her home at the Vineyard

04:53.410 --> 04:55.777
for three weeks, rent-free.

04:55.838 --> 04:57.370
How come I'm not coming?

04:57.464 --> 04:59.689
Well, that was
her one condition.

04:59.750 --> 05:01.374
D'oh!

05:01.468 --> 05:04.194
Aw, I'm gonna
miss you all so much.

05:04.212 --> 05:05.637
Well, at least
I'll have the dog.

05:05.789 --> 05:08.698
Sorry, Dad. We put the pets
with Mr. Flanders

05:08.759 --> 05:11.868
because, well,
we knew he'd take care of them.

05:11.887 --> 05:12.978
(whistling)

05:13.129 --> 05:15.314
-Come to papa.
-(barking, meowing)

05:15.482 --> 05:17.057
(grunts)
Good, good.

05:17.151 --> 05:18.299
Make-believe you love him.

05:18.360 --> 05:21.227
-Flanders, I love you!
-D'oh!

05:21.322 --> 05:24.397
We're staying at my Aunt Edith's
house at Hyannibunkport.

05:24.550 --> 05:27.233
It's south of Squibagansett,
east of Codtucket,

05:27.328 --> 05:29.219
next to Little Crabkill Bog.

05:29.279 --> 05:31.738
Those are great names.
You'll never want to leave.

05:31.874 --> 05:35.250
I'm gonna keep you in my sight
as long as I can.

05:37.362 --> 05:39.004
-♪ ♪
-(thunder rumbles)

05:44.720 --> 05:46.086
(horn honking)

05:46.221 --> 05:49.255
We love you! Stop following!

05:49.350 --> 05:50.832
(fading):
Okay.

05:50.893 --> 05:52.559
(horn honks)

05:53.878 --> 05:56.355
(buzzing)

05:56.548 --> 06:00.417
♪<i> ...drink it up,</i>
<i> then throw me out the door</i> ♪

06:00.519 --> 06:02.419
♪<i> I've traveled in England</i> ♪

06:02.479 --> 06:05.088
♪<i> I've traveled in France</i> ♪

06:05.107 --> 06:10.427
♪<i> At a hint of good music,</i>
<i> I'll sing or I'll dance</i> ♪

06:10.445 --> 06:15.265
♪<i> So hear me, then, mister,</i>
<i> and pour me one more...</i> ♪

06:15.283 --> 06:17.267
Gentlemen...

06:17.285 --> 06:21.588
♪<i> If I can't drink it up,</i>
<i> then throw me out the door.</i> ♪

06:23.291 --> 06:24.699
(laughter)

06:24.760 --> 06:27.219
You have to seize life
and relish every minute.

06:27.412 --> 06:29.054
Eliminate all sorrow.

06:29.223 --> 06:31.706
Open a bloody window.

06:31.767 --> 06:33.558
♪<i> Hallelujah.</i> ♪

06:33.710 --> 06:35.685
Okay, okay,
that's enough of that.

06:36.721 --> 06:39.289
(Satanic music plays)

06:39.391 --> 06:41.641
♪<i> Hallelujah.</i> ♪

06:41.793 --> 06:43.551
(Satanic music plays)

06:43.654 --> 06:45.237
-♪<i> Ha...</i> ♪
-(Satanic music plays)

06:45.430 --> 06:47.889
Hey, Lily, you like suspenders?
'Cause I got them.

06:47.991 --> 06:50.984
Well, I hope you don't mind
if I give them a wee snap.

06:51.078 --> 06:53.653
-(laughs softly)
-Ooh! Intimacy.

06:53.789 --> 06:57.641
Lily, you've transformed this
dump into a joint. Bless you.

06:57.701 --> 06:59.233
(crying)

06:59.294 --> 07:01.661
(moans sadly)

07:01.755 --> 07:04.423
-♪ ♪
-(gasps)

07:04.591 --> 07:06.425
(sighs)

07:08.804 --> 07:11.245
Who are you?

07:11.306 --> 07:13.598
-Homer Simpson.
-You know, Homer,

07:13.791 --> 07:17.102
I've never met a man who didn't
offer me his chair or his beer.

07:17.295 --> 07:19.329
-You have now.
-So, tell me,

07:19.389 --> 07:20.847
what's wrong with you?

07:20.999 --> 07:22.256
Mm, it's personal.

07:22.401 --> 07:25.259
Tell me. Maybe I can
lighten your load.

07:25.320 --> 07:28.171
-My family left me
for three weeks.
-No.

07:28.231 --> 07:30.356
The dog and cat
are with Flanders.

07:30.451 --> 07:31.675
Oh!

07:31.735 --> 07:34.286
I'm alone.
I don't know what to do.

07:36.123 --> 07:38.457
You have to have a good time
for their sake,

07:38.650 --> 07:40.850
because if you don't,
they'll feel guilty

07:40.952 --> 07:42.018
and never forgive you.

07:42.120 --> 07:43.795
And you'll never forgive them,

07:43.947 --> 07:46.022
because they're causing you
the misery.

07:46.124 --> 07:48.115
And you'll all be buried
in dirty laundry

07:48.135 --> 07:50.635
with squealing kids
for the rest of your days.

07:50.828 --> 07:52.545
Wow. Wow.

07:52.698 --> 07:56.123
You're the smartest woman
I've ever met in my life.

07:56.226 --> 07:57.684
Except one.

07:58.645 --> 08:00.386
Shut the window!

08:00.539 --> 08:01.813
But then everything
smells like you.

08:02.006 --> 08:04.465
-(both grunting)
-Take that.

08:04.526 --> 08:06.693
(phone ringing)

08:10.157 --> 08:15.160
♪<i> Anticipation</i> ♪

08:15.353 --> 08:21.241
♪<i> Anticipation</i>
<i> is making me late...</i> ♪

08:21.335 --> 08:23.243
Welcome to our tour
of the Vineyard.

08:23.337 --> 08:26.988
This is where Steven Spielberg
shot<i> Jaws.</i>

08:27.090 --> 08:28.823
That's the end of our tour.

08:28.842 --> 08:31.084
Now, my aunt's house
is only eight miles away.

08:31.178 --> 08:34.387
But we just have
to make it before sundown.

08:38.560 --> 08:41.911
Uh, Mom, I think
you've gone off the road.

08:41.972 --> 08:43.913
Whoa, watch out for that deer!

08:43.974 --> 08:45.339
(gasps)

08:45.359 --> 08:48.109
-That was close.
-(shouts) More deer!

08:49.254 --> 08:51.696
(thudding, tires screeching)

08:51.889 --> 08:53.514
(sighs)
We're here.

08:53.534 --> 08:55.683
-(thunder crashes)
-(groans)

08:55.744 --> 08:57.202
<i> -(laughter)</i>
<i> -CARL: Your turn, Lily.</i>

08:57.395 --> 08:59.445
(clicking, beeping)

08:59.540 --> 09:01.355
(fanfare plays)

09:01.458 --> 09:02.432
(moans)

09:02.492 --> 09:05.785
I miss them. I miss them.

09:05.937 --> 09:09.530
It's been so long.
No one to comfort me.

09:09.550 --> 09:14.052
Put your mobile away, because
I'm gonna sing in German.

09:14.245 --> 09:17.088
♪<i> Vor der Kaserne</i> ♪

09:17.224 --> 09:19.540
♪<i> Vor dem grossen Tor</i> ♪

09:19.601 --> 09:22.376
♪<i> Stand eine Laterne</i> ♪

09:22.396 --> 09:24.621
♪<i> Und steht sie noch davor...</i> ♪

09:24.681 --> 09:27.290
This is like that beautiful
scene in<i> Sound of Music</i>

09:27.392 --> 09:30.310
when all the Nazis
sang good night.

09:30.462 --> 09:35.056
♪<i> Wie einst Lili Marleen</i> ♪

09:35.117 --> 09:36.983
♪<i> Wie einst</i> ♪

09:37.077 --> 09:40.120
♪<i> Lili Marleen.</i> ♪

09:41.773 --> 09:44.499
If you're done singing,
can we turn up the game?

09:46.402 --> 09:50.071
(gasps, cries)

09:50.090 --> 09:51.998
-(crying)
-What's wrong, lady?

09:52.092 --> 09:54.183
We miss you inside.

09:54.210 --> 09:55.835
A good bloke
who never had a break,

09:55.929 --> 09:57.153
and now has a broken spirit.

09:57.255 --> 09:59.322
He's lost and lonely,

09:59.341 --> 10:02.158
and really doesn't
give a fig about me.

10:02.218 --> 10:05.419
-I'm in love.
-I love him, too.

10:05.522 --> 10:07.105
(both sigh)

10:12.154 --> 10:13.519
Okay. The sun is shining.

10:13.672 --> 10:16.689
(exhales)
I can finally read my book.

10:16.825 --> 10:18.524
(seabird chirping)

10:18.619 --> 10:22.287
Hello, nature.
Time to meet your death.

10:23.239 --> 10:25.957
♪ ♪

10:26.109 --> 10:27.792
(gasps)
Bart, those are tick bites!

10:27.985 --> 10:29.369
You'll get Lyme disease.

10:29.504 --> 10:31.421
Why didn't somebody warn me?

10:33.842 --> 10:37.260
-(Marge grunts)
-(groans)

10:38.996 --> 10:40.287
Get me a priest.

10:40.349 --> 10:43.032
Mom, I always liked you.

10:43.093 --> 10:44.717
Oh, honey, try to relax.

10:44.811 --> 10:46.202
Watch<i> Itchy & Scratchy!</i>

10:46.221 --> 10:48.480
I am itchy and scratchy.

10:48.673 --> 10:50.815
Meanwhile,
Homer little dreamed that...

10:50.967 --> 10:53.226
Willie! Do you think it would
kill you to rake and talk?

10:53.320 --> 10:55.320
Would you rather
I tell the story

10:55.489 --> 10:58.047
about what's under
these leaves and dirt?

10:58.066 --> 10:59.473
(Skinner groans)

10:59.493 --> 11:02.143
Oh. No. No, no, no, no,
no, no, no. Carry on.

11:02.204 --> 11:03.569
(chuckles nervously)

11:03.722 --> 11:06.147
Getting back,
Lily continued to light up

11:06.208 --> 11:09.334
all the men's lives,
except Homer's.

11:10.253 --> 11:11.318
BOTH:
Lily!

11:11.338 --> 11:12.395
Gentlemen.

11:12.455 --> 11:14.155
I made you all picnic lunches.

11:14.216 --> 11:15.231
-Yeah!
-Wow!

11:15.291 --> 11:16.157
It's British food.

11:16.259 --> 11:17.083
BOTH:
Oh...

11:17.219 --> 11:19.252
Post-1990 British food.

11:19.388 --> 11:20.586
BOTH:
Yes!

11:20.722 --> 11:22.764
♪ ♪

11:25.852 --> 11:28.687
Smithers,
that woman has captivated me,

11:28.838 --> 11:30.096
which, if memory serves,

11:30.190 --> 11:32.190
is an early state
of physical arousal.

11:32.383 --> 11:33.841
Sir, we've been
through this before

11:33.902 --> 11:36.753
with several women
and one very shapely tree.

11:36.771 --> 11:38.196
I feel a tingle I haven't felt

11:38.389 --> 11:40.014
since they took the cocaine
out of Coca-Cola.

11:40.075 --> 11:41.849
I must woo her.

11:41.910 --> 11:43.702
And Simpson's my way in.

11:43.853 --> 11:45.686
Have him ask her
on a date on my boat

11:45.747 --> 11:47.872
which will actually be
a date with me.

11:48.024 --> 11:50.858
But, sir, why not have me
ask her directly?

11:50.919 --> 11:52.452
(laughs)
As if I could trust you

11:52.587 --> 11:54.103
to keep your hands off a lady.

11:54.164 --> 11:56.956
(forced chuckle)
How well you know me, sir.

11:57.092 --> 11:59.217
♪ ♪

12:01.337 --> 12:03.430
<i> HOMER:</i>
<i> Uh-oh.</i>

12:04.391 --> 12:06.373
Very good, Maggie!

12:06.435 --> 12:09.185
Now we can cook them. Num-num!

12:13.591 --> 12:15.900
(horn blares)

12:16.069 --> 12:17.551
Who are all those people?

12:17.654 --> 12:19.979
It's the weekenders
from Falmouth.

12:20.115 --> 12:21.297
(horn blares)

12:21.357 --> 12:22.723
It's almost here.

12:22.826 --> 12:25.702
And raise the prices...

12:33.086 --> 12:34.711
...now!

12:41.336 --> 12:42.335
Clam strips and beer!

12:42.429 --> 12:44.411
MAN:
Black Dog mousepads!

12:44.473 --> 12:45.838
-MAN 2: Over here!
-MAN 3: T-shirts!

12:45.991 --> 12:48.183
MAN 4:
CDs by James Taylor's brother!

12:50.687 --> 12:52.253
-Hyah!
-Hyah!

12:52.355 --> 12:54.847
ALL:
Hyah! Hyah! Hyah!
Hyah! Hyah! Hyah!

12:54.941 --> 12:57.275
That's it! We're going home.

12:59.971 --> 13:03.764
Everyone was innocently falling
into Burns's trap.

13:03.825 --> 13:08.620
And trouble brewed as
Lily offered a perverse prayer.

13:08.813 --> 13:10.604
-♪ ♪
-(seabird screeching)

13:10.665 --> 13:12.031
(bell dings)

13:12.959 --> 13:13.958
<i> LILY:</i>
<i> Forgive me, Lord.</i>

13:14.110 --> 13:15.293
<i> I must have Homer.</i>

13:15.444 --> 13:17.353
<i> Please let me win him,</i>
<i> even briefly.</i>

13:17.372 --> 13:20.023
<i> It would be like having</i>
<i> a lover and a child</i>

13:20.124 --> 13:21.716
<i> at the same time.</i>

13:23.878 --> 13:25.361
Hey, Lily. How you doin'?

13:25.421 --> 13:27.806
Homer! I'm so glad
you asked me to meet you here.

13:27.999 --> 13:29.474
Thanks, I'm glad
you feel that way.

13:29.667 --> 13:31.292
But there's something
I didn't tell you.

13:31.353 --> 13:33.719
Uh... you're on a date
with my boss.

13:33.814 --> 13:34.887
That's my boat.

13:34.981 --> 13:37.223
♪ ♪

13:37.359 --> 13:39.484
My name is Montgomery Burns.

13:39.635 --> 13:43.046
I'm the richest and therefore
most attractive man in town.

13:43.106 --> 13:44.213
Okay, see ya.

13:44.274 --> 13:45.715
Wait, wait, wait, Mr. Burns!

13:45.775 --> 13:48.159
Surely a venerable gentleman
such as yourself

13:48.352 --> 13:50.311
would know that
I need a chaperone.

13:50.372 --> 13:52.555
Of course.
Simpson, join us.

13:52.615 --> 13:55.083
Smithers, cue my weapon of woo.

13:56.211 --> 13:59.963
♪ ♪

14:00.957 --> 14:03.174
I know a shortcut.

14:08.464 --> 14:10.849
<i> HOMER:</i>
<i> Why am I staring at her?</i>

14:11.042 --> 14:13.017
<i> I'll make my eyes</i>
<i> look at something else.</i>

14:18.358 --> 14:20.191
<i> Oh, my God.</i>

14:20.384 --> 14:22.277
<i> I'm smiling back.</i>

14:25.365 --> 14:28.199
I hope you enjoyed
your dinner. (chuckles)

14:28.351 --> 14:30.517
And just wait till we get
to dessert.

14:30.620 --> 14:32.186
You make me feel like
I'm having dinner

14:32.247 --> 14:33.854
with a James Bond villain.

14:33.957 --> 14:35.022
(chuckles)

14:35.125 --> 14:36.207
She gets me.

14:36.400 --> 14:38.418
Now, wink for me, Smithers.

14:40.046 --> 14:42.505
(chuckling)

14:45.242 --> 14:47.218
(sighs)
What am I doing here?

14:50.915 --> 14:53.783
<i> HOMER:</i>
<i> What have I done</i>
<i> to this wonderful woman?</i>

14:53.885 --> 14:56.144
<i> How can I make it up to her?</i>

14:57.722 --> 14:58.955
I'm sorry.

14:59.015 --> 15:00.381
Why did you bring me here?

15:00.400 --> 15:01.715
Fear of unemployment.

15:01.735 --> 15:04.569
Um, let's just stay
through dessert.

15:06.356 --> 15:08.239
Look at me!
I'm Gypsy Rose Lee!

15:08.391 --> 15:11.150
You and me and
my cardiologist make three!

15:11.244 --> 15:13.227
Sorry, I have to leave
right now.

15:13.246 --> 15:14.579
Oh. But why?

15:14.772 --> 15:17.640
I just spilled
a glass of wine on myself.

15:17.700 --> 15:19.083
Also, this bottle.

15:19.252 --> 15:21.294
Homer, let's go.

15:22.797 --> 15:23.829
Whoa.

15:23.924 --> 15:25.590
That was awful.

15:25.741 --> 15:27.316
There's some people
that make you feel

15:27.377 --> 15:29.652
being lonely isn't so bad.

15:29.671 --> 15:31.412
And there are people
that make you

15:31.473 --> 15:33.080
never want to be lonely again.

15:33.099 --> 15:34.933
(laughs)
I hear ya.

15:35.126 --> 15:36.342
And I almost understand ya.

15:36.436 --> 15:37.994
Thank God
you were there to save me.

15:38.012 --> 15:39.420
That's what I'm best at:

15:39.522 --> 15:41.755
saving people from things
I get them into.

15:41.775 --> 15:43.424
(giggles)
You've got a little cake

15:43.485 --> 15:44.776
on the corner of your mouth.

15:44.945 --> 15:46.018
Oh, I do? Where?

15:46.112 --> 15:47.353
-Just here.
-There?

15:47.505 --> 15:48.838
-Just there.
-Oh-- Where?

15:48.898 --> 15:50.690
-Right there?
-Just-- You're missing it.

15:50.825 --> 15:52.191
-There?
-Just to the...

15:52.285 --> 15:54.285
-Oh, just let me do it.
-Okay.

15:55.664 --> 15:57.121
You can stop now.

15:57.314 --> 16:00.016
Uh... I meant go slow.

16:00.034 --> 16:01.534
Uh, wait a minute, wait.

16:01.686 --> 16:03.628
While you're there,
could you get the upper lip?

16:06.374 --> 16:08.357
(laughs softly)
Oh, my God,

16:08.418 --> 16:09.950
what am I going to do with you?

16:09.970 --> 16:10.802
Please, nothing.

16:10.995 --> 16:12.971
I'm taking you home now.

16:15.166 --> 16:17.308
♪ ♪

16:28.771 --> 16:31.472
Well, aren't you going
to walk me in?

16:31.533 --> 16:32.991
(whimpers)

16:33.184 --> 16:34.659
Look, Lily.

16:34.852 --> 16:36.310
You're the most... Um...

16:36.329 --> 16:37.495
Finish that thought.

16:37.688 --> 16:39.238
You're the most anything
of any woman

16:39.390 --> 16:40.723
I've ever known
except for my wife.

16:40.742 --> 16:42.892
Who I loved-- I mean love!
I said "love!"

16:42.910 --> 16:43.668
Oh, that's beautiful.

16:43.819 --> 16:45.152
Thank you.

16:45.213 --> 16:47.321
But give me one damn
proper kiss goodbye.

16:47.424 --> 16:48.673
No.

16:49.676 --> 16:51.175
♪ ♪

16:51.368 --> 16:53.069
(Homer whimpering)

16:53.129 --> 16:55.430
(moaning)

16:59.001 --> 17:00.409
No. No!

17:00.428 --> 17:01.594
This is good,

17:01.688 --> 17:03.521
but is it worth
burning in hell forever?

17:03.672 --> 17:05.097
We'll see each other
in our dreams,

17:05.191 --> 17:06.357
whether you like it or not.

17:06.526 --> 17:08.175
You stay out of my dreams!

17:08.236 --> 17:10.028
All my stuff's in there!

17:16.369 --> 17:17.410
Gotta stay awake. If I dream
of Lily, it's all over.

17:20.206 --> 17:23.023
Gotta stay awake.
Gotta stay awake.

17:23.126 --> 17:24.767
Must not dream.

17:24.786 --> 17:28.421
Gotta stay awake.
Gotta stay awake.

17:28.572 --> 17:29.622
Oh, no.

17:29.716 --> 17:31.698
(snores)

17:31.760 --> 17:33.109
♪ ♪

17:33.127 --> 17:34.627
(giggles)

17:34.721 --> 17:37.280
You've got a little cake
on the corner of your mouth.

17:37.298 --> 17:39.965
-Homer? Homer?
-(mutters) She's here.

17:40.060 --> 17:41.801
She's here and God help me,

17:41.895 --> 17:43.286
-I'm glad.
-Homer.

17:43.387 --> 17:45.137
-Marge!
-Surprise!

17:45.290 --> 17:46.547
We came back early.

17:46.608 --> 17:48.457
Oh, thank God.
Oh, thank God!

17:48.559 --> 17:50.401
I'll never let you go a...

17:50.553 --> 17:51.460
(phone vibrates)

17:51.521 --> 17:52.987
Who's calling you so late?

17:53.722 --> 17:55.073
Telemarketer.

17:55.266 --> 17:56.799
Gotta take it.

17:56.859 --> 17:59.118
Those people are so sensitive.

18:01.581 --> 18:03.806
-Hello?
-(falsetto): Wrong number!

18:03.866 --> 18:05.308
-Homer?
-Damn it!

18:05.368 --> 18:07.660
-I need to see you now, Homer.
-(whimpers)

18:07.812 --> 18:09.069
You know the address.

18:09.130 --> 18:11.314
Lovers Lane,
just off Fidelity Avenue.

18:11.374 --> 18:13.240
Listen.
I have to tell you right now

18:13.301 --> 18:14.926
I can never see you again.

18:15.119 --> 18:16.743
Can you tell me in person?

18:16.805 --> 18:18.245
Great idea.

18:18.264 --> 18:20.264
Keep me on the line.
I'll guide you here.

18:20.416 --> 18:21.582
Ooh...

18:21.684 --> 18:23.509
You realize
nothing's gonna happen.

18:23.661 --> 18:25.252
Of course.

18:25.355 --> 18:28.998
♪<i> I promise you chocolate</i>
<i> and kisses</i> ♪

18:29.058 --> 18:33.169
♪<i> Martinis with lemon drops...</i> ♪

18:33.229 --> 18:35.095
♪ ♪

18:35.156 --> 18:37.022
No, feet! No!

18:37.117 --> 18:38.991
(sighs)

18:40.144 --> 18:41.527
♪<i> I just woke up</i> ♪

18:41.621 --> 18:46.666
♪<i> And made you pork chops...</i> ♪

18:48.336 --> 18:50.110
♪<i> La, la, la</i> ♪

18:50.171 --> 18:52.188
♪<i> La, la,</i>
<i> la</i> ♪

18:52.248 --> 18:54.540
♪<i> La, la, la</i> ♪

18:54.634 --> 18:56.950
-♪<i> La, la, la</i> ♪
<i> -MARGE:</i> ♪<i> La, la, la</i> ♪

18:57.011 --> 18:59.378
<i> -LILY:</i> ♪<i> La, la, la</i> ♪
<i> -MARGE:</i> ♪<i> La, la, la</i> ♪

18:59.472 --> 19:02.031
♪<i> La, la, la</i> ♪

19:02.091 --> 19:06.218
♪<i> La, la, la, la, la, la</i> ♪

19:06.354 --> 19:09.630
♪<i> La, la, la, la, la...</i> ♪

19:09.691 --> 19:11.149
Pork chops!

19:11.300 --> 19:12.391
♪<i> La, la, la</i> ♪

19:12.485 --> 19:14.318
♪<i> La, la,</i>
<i> la</i> ♪

19:14.487 --> 19:18.656
♪<i> La, la, la.</i> ♪

19:18.825 --> 19:20.749
You're home.

19:20.818 --> 19:21.659
Yes, I am.

19:21.852 --> 19:23.052
And I'll never leave you.

19:23.154 --> 19:24.662
There might be frequent
interruptions.

19:24.813 --> 19:25.997
I may stop at Moe's,

19:26.190 --> 19:27.814
I may be watching
the hot dogs spin

19:27.834 --> 19:29.167
at the movie theater,

19:29.318 --> 19:32.486
or I may be picking
a flower for you...

19:32.589 --> 19:35.581
but I will never,
ever leave you.

19:35.675 --> 19:37.675
Aw, Homie.

19:40.555 --> 19:42.722
(sobbing)

19:46.210 --> 19:49.520
<i> ANNOUNCER:</i>
<i> Now boarding, non-stop</i>
<i> Springfield to London.</i>

19:49.689 --> 19:51.189
<i> Sorry, lady.</i>

19:57.030 --> 19:58.087
How was America, dear?

19:58.147 --> 19:59.680
There's nothing there for me.

19:59.741 --> 20:02.033
It's big, full of fried food,
and heartbreaking...

20:02.202 --> 20:04.276
and that's just one man.

20:04.370 --> 20:06.954
There'll never be another
like him.

20:10.493 --> 20:11.951
Buy you a drink, sweetheart?

20:12.086 --> 20:13.118
No.

20:13.254 --> 20:14.453
Fancy a drink?

20:14.605 --> 20:15.287
No, thank you.

20:15.381 --> 20:17.048
Would you get-- No.

20:17.241 --> 20:18.382
No. No thanks.

20:18.575 --> 20:19.700
Get off.

20:19.719 --> 20:21.385
BRITISH MAN:
Buy you a corndog?

20:21.578 --> 20:24.388
(gasps) Yes!
But first, are you married?

20:24.581 --> 20:26.557
And would you shave off
the mustache?

20:26.750 --> 20:29.227
Yes, and immediately.

